<span id="freeTextContainer10690123304881343332">I almost gave up on this book early on. I&apos;m glad I didn&apos;t. While I didn&apos;t really care for the character of Ruth too much or her life in San Fransisco, the story of her mother LuLing really saved the book and turned the entire novel into a deeply affecting work. The middle act where LuLing is allowed to tell her story in her own words was the obvious high point of the book for me. </span>
  <span id="freeText10690123304881343332" style="display:none">I almost gave up on this book early on. I'm glad I didn't. While I didn't really care for the character of Ruth too much or her life in San Fransisco, the story of her mother LuLing really saved the book and turned the entire novel into a deeply affecting work. The middle act where LuLing is allowed to tell her story in her own words was the obvious high point of the book for me. </span>
