    <a title="Suzanne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/888138-suzanne"><img alt="Suzanne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1355673827p2/888138.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/14899365?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Suzanne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Suzanne" href="/user/show/888138-suzanne">Suzanne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/888138-suzanne?shelf=chinese-women-s-writing">chinese-women-s-writing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/888138-suzanne?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/888138-suzanne?shelf=summer-read">summer-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer14899365" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7034107832961481573">I just didn&apos;t enjoy this as much as Amy Tan&apos;s other books. Her plot development, with its mother-daughter issues, has become almost a formula. She does do a credible job describing life in China in the last century and I came away with a deeper understanding of that culture. I just never thought of Amy Tan as the Maeve Binchy of Asian writing. This is not meant to be a criticism of Maeve Binchy, an author whose well-written books I think are fun to read. It just is I get the impression that she </span>
  <span id="freeText7034107832961481573" style="display:none">I just didn't enjoy this as much as Amy Tan's other books. Her plot development, with its mother-daughter issues, has become almost a formula. She does do a credible job describing life in China in the last century and I came away with a deeper understanding of that culture. I just never thought of Amy Tan as the Maeve Binchy of Asian writing. This is not meant to be a criticism of Maeve Binchy, an author whose well-written books I think are fun to read. It just is I get the impression that she keeps writing the same story, just changing the locations a little and adding nuances to the characters. That is how I am beginning to feel about Amy Tan. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7034107832961481573" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


