    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_930262211" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/930262211" />
    <a title="Bookworm" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31167656-bookworm"><img alt="Bookworm" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1508209904p2/31167656.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/930262211?book_show_action=true">Mar 08, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bookworm" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bookworm" href="/user/show/31167656-bookworm">Bookworm</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer930262211" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12875288318079462834">The Bonesetter&apos;s Daughter was a beautiful and complicated story about maternal lineage, Chinese culture and family bonds. An absolutely mesmerizing and heartwrenching tale that focuses on the lives of 3 generations of the well respected and famous bonesetter from a small Chinese village.<br/><br/>The author has a gift for creating a story rich in history and emotion. The plot spans from early 20th century to present day. It takes place in Peking, Hong Kong and North America.<br/><br/>This is a slower moving tale th</span>
  <span id="freeText12875288318079462834" style="display:none">The Bonesetter's Daughter was a beautiful and complicated story about maternal lineage, Chinese culture and family bonds. An absolutely mesmerizing and heartwrenching tale that focuses on the lives of 3 generations of the well respected and famous bonesetter from a small Chinese village.<br /><br />The author has a gift for creating a story rich in history and emotion. The plot spans from early 20th century to present day. It takes place in Peking, Hong Kong and North America.<br /><br />This is a slower moving tale that takes its time. We get to know and understand Ruth, her mother and Precious Auntie very well. By the end, old secrets are revealed and life lessons are learned. A beautiful end to a beautiful story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12875288318079462834" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


